		"body": "**Description**\r\nEnable \"Cut\" and \"Copy\" actions for images in the Markdown editor's context menu.\r\n\r\n**Changes:**\r\n- Modified [contextMenu.ts](cci:7://file:///Users/RohitKumar/Desktop/joplin/packages/app-desktop/gui/NoteEditor/utils/contextMenu.ts:0:0-0:0) to remove the image-type restriction for Cut/Copy actions.\r\n- Updated the CodeMirror [useContextMenu](cci:1://file:///Users/RohitKumar/Desktop/joplin/packages/app-desktop/gui/NoteEditor/NoteBody/CodeMirror/utils/useContextMenu.ts:117:0-386:2) hook to accurately calculate the Markdown markup range for images, allowing the \"Cut\" action to correctly remove the markup.\r\n- **Refinement:** Added logic to respect the editor's read-only state (disabling \"Cut\" but allowing \"Copy\" in read-only notes).\r\n- **Refinement:** Cleaned up TypeScript types and fixed linting issues identified by automated feedback.\r\n\r\n**Test Plan:**\r\n1. Insert an image into a Markdown note.\r\n2. Right-click the image in the editor.\r\n3. Verify \"Cut\" removes the `![]()` markup and copies the image to the clipboard.\r\n4. Verify \"Copy\" copies the image to the clipboard without removing markup.\r\n5. Verify \"Cut\" is disabled when the note is in a read-only state (e.g., viewing Note History).\r\n\r\nI have read the CLA Document and I hereby sign the CLA.\r\n",
