			"body": "Hi Laurent, my apologies for the confusion!\r\n\r\nIssue Reference: The reference to #11599 was a mistake in my commit message (likely a typo for a different issue I was researching). I'm sorry for the noise there.\r\nCopy Markdown: While 'Copy Image' handles the binary data, I noticed there was no way to copy the actual Markdown link (![alt](:/id)) directly from the context menu in the editor. I thought this would be useful for moving images around within notes.\r\nCut Action: I understand if 'Cut' isn't a priority for images.\r\nSince you've already implemented the image context menu recently, I'll close this if you feel these additions are redundant. Thank you for the feedback!",
